description: For sale in our Atlanta showroom is a survivor 1973 Chevrolet Corvette. A two-owner car, this Corvette has been meticulously taken care of. Numbers matching, this C3 Corvette is a real sight for sore eyes. This '73 Corvette for sale is powered by a factory optioned 350 cubic inch small block Chevy V8 engine. Built from the factory with an 8.5:1 compression, this small block powered '73 Corvette for sale is built healthy and puts out an impressive 270 foot pounds of torque. With a nostalgic burble echoing through dual exhaust, you're going to be grinning ear to ear as you launch from every stoplight. Backed by a 3-speed automatic transmission this Vette for sale is a joy to run through the gears.  With power brakes and power steering, this Corvette moves and stops just as well as it accelerates.  The exterior on this C3 beauty is a GM lover's dream, dressed head to toe in a smooth shade of White. The color hugs every curve of this Stingray for sale, showing of the voluptuous lines of this bowtie classic. Remodeled from the previous year,  the muscular approach was ditched, in an effort to build more of a touring oriented car.  With the T-Tops off, it's just begging for you to turn your Friday night tour into a weekend-long journey! With long drives in mind, you'll definitely want an interior that's just as eager to please. The Tan vinyl interior is sporty, especially when wrapped around a pair sport bucket seats. Pleasantly straddling the shifter, this Corvette for sale was built to drive.  Taking a seat, you feel like the pilot of your own fighter jet, with a cockpit adorned with a plethora of gauges. Options on this 1973 Chevrolet Corvette for sale, includes: A/C , AM/FM radio, CD player, T-tops, power brakes, power steering, seat belts, vinyl interior, and Corvette rally wheels wrapped in raised white letter radial tires. Now's your chance to get into one fun cruising Chevy! For those people who have been looking for the original Corvette Stingray of their dreams, this is it!. For more information please call the Atlanta showroom at 678-894-4833 or e-mail us at Atlanta@GatewayClassicCars.com.
title: 1973 Chevrolet Corvette

description: Complete Restoration / Original 400ci Engine Completely Rebuilt / Factory AC

This truck was recently restored to “like new” condition.  At 55000, this is a low mileage truck for its age.  A new frame-on restoration includes the refinishing or replacement of over 80% of this truck.   The paint was refinished in 2 stage two-tone Chevy Terrace Blue & White that shines like glass over a rust free body.  New NOS trim all the way around including the grill, and, chrome bumpers are as good as new.  Even the Chevy Emblem on the front grill is NOS new. The Interior seating is original and in excellent condition especially for its age.  There is one small 2? scrape to the drivers side stitching (as shown) but there are no tares to the material at all.  Door panels, carpet, headliner and the steering wheel are NOS new.  The entire dash has been repainted to match the body color as it was from the factory.  The dash pad is crack free..The original AM radio has been replaced by a modern aftermarket system.  All features and gauges work properly.

The original matching numbers 400 engine was just rebuilt and has less than 100 miles since.  There are no fluid leaks of any kind.  The radiator is brand new as well.  In addition to being a beautiful show piece, this truck can be driven everyday, all day.  A new Rhino Liner bed liner not only looks great but allows this truck to do what it was meant to do; Work!  The option is yours.  This is a rare version of this truck having the factory 400ci engine.   Most were built with the a Chevy 350ci engine.  This truck also comes equipped with factory AC. It runs beautifully, starts immediately and cruises easily on highways. Brakes and tires are ready for inspection.  Nothing is needed.  We are proud to offer this beautifully restored, highly desirable C10 pickup with the best of many worlds.  The looks of a fine classic pickup and the power and ability to take on work loads and long relaxing drives. Test drives are welcome!
